cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper deals with distributed optimization of submodular functions, which is a problem in both theoretical computer science (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of MapReduce style computations suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC). The applications mentioned in the abstract, such as clustering and Gaussian process inference, are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and signal processing (cs.SI).
